  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --localstatedir=/var \
            --disable-logger \
            --disable-syslogd &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--disable-logger</parameter>: This switch prevents inetutils
        from installing the <command>logger</command> program since a better
        version is installed by util-linux.
      </para>

      <para>
        <parameter>--disable-syslogd</parameter>: This switch prevents inetutils
        from installing the System Log Daemon, which is installed with the
        sysklogd package. 
      </para>

    </sect3>

